de.dosmike.sponge.megamenus.api.elements

Class MSpinner

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.dosmike.sponge.megamenus.impl.elements.IElementImpl
      • de.dosmike.sponge.megamenus.api.elements.MSpinner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IClickable<MSpinner>, IElement, IPressable<MSpinner>, IValueChangeable<org.spongepowered.api.text.Text,MSpinner>, org.spongepowered.api.util.Identifiable

    public final class MSpinner
extends IElementImpl
implements IClickable<MSpinner>, IPressable<MSpinner>, IValueChangeable<org.spongepowered.api.text.Text,MSpinner>
    This element displays a cyclic value. Compared to the checkbox this can have more values and custom icons (icons won't display in text UIs)

      • copy

        public MSpinner copy()
        Description copied from interface: IElement
        It is quicker for the elements to implement this method, than to use reflection to determine field to copy. Example: A Button extends IElement should implement this as 
         public Button copy() {
   Button copy = new Button(...);
   ... // element specific values to copy
   return copy;
 }
        Specified by:
        copy in interface IElement
        Returns:
        a copy of this element with the same values
